resources.string: To open the next view, leave the login and the password fields empty.
An example of saving UI states of a multi-pane window
This screen represents the login operation. The purpose of this screen is to show the possibility to save ui state after changing configuration like screen rotation.

This is an example of using the Timer Service and the Timer Broadcast Receiver. The service runs for 20 seconds, every second it sends a broadcast and stops at the end. The service can run in background without any bound user interface components.
